WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:21.760
The Fisherman and His Soul by Oscar Wilde Copyright Blackcat Publishing

00:21.760 --> 00:26.880
Chapter 1 The Mermaid

00:26.880 --> 00:31.560
Every evening the Fisherman went out fishing.

00:31.560 --> 00:35.120
He sometimes sold his fish at the market.

00:35.120 --> 00:40.960
Sometimes he did not catch many fish and he could not sell them.

00:40.960 --> 00:44.760
One evening his net was very heavy.

00:44.760 --> 00:54.200
He laughed and said, did I catch all the fish in the sea or did I catch some horrible

00:54.200 --> 00:55.840
monster?

00:55.840 --> 00:58.480
I will give it to the queen.

00:58.480 --> 01:00.600
She will be happy.

01:00.600 --> 01:04.440
He pulled and pulled the heavy net.

01:04.440 --> 01:08.760
Finally he pulled the net next to the boat.

01:08.760 --> 01:14.280
But there were no fish in it and there was no monster.

01:14.280 --> 01:17.600
There was only a little mermaid.

01:17.600 --> 01:20.000
She was asleep.

01:20.000 --> 01:23.280
Her hair was yellow like gold.

01:23.280 --> 01:27.160
Her body was white like ivory.

01:27.160 --> 01:35.000
Her tail like silver and pearl and her ears like seashells.

01:35.000 --> 01:37.960
She was very beautiful.

01:37.960 --> 01:41.720
The Fisherman pulled the net closer to the boat.

01:41.720 --> 01:43.800
She embraced her.

01:43.800 --> 01:48.240
When he touched her she screamed.

01:48.240 --> 01:56.160
She could not escape so she began to cry and said, please let me go.

01:56.160 --> 01:59.800
I am the only daughter of the king of the sea.

01:59.800 --> 02:04.360
My father is very old and alone.

02:04.360 --> 02:11.200
But the Fisherman answered her, I will let you go but you must make me a promise.

02:12.120 --> 02:17.120
I will call you and you will come and sing to me.

02:17.120 --> 02:21.760
The fish love the songs of the people of the sea.

02:21.760 --> 02:25.600
You will sing and my nets will be full.

02:25.600 --> 02:31.440
I promise, please let me go cried the mermaid.

02:31.440 --> 02:41.120
Yes, I will let you go said the Fisherman so she promised him and he let her go.

02:41.120 --> 02:45.160
She went back into the sea and trembled.

02:45.160 --> 02:49.040
She felt a strange fear.

02:49.040 --> 02:55.080
Every evening the young Fisherman went fishing and called the mermaid.

02:55.080 --> 02:58.760
She came and sang to him.

02:58.760 --> 03:02.120
The dolphin swam round and round her.

03:02.120 --> 03:06.160
The seagulls were in the sky above her head.

03:06.160 --> 03:12.720
She sang a marvelous song of the tritons, the men with long green beards.

03:12.720 --> 03:17.160
She sang of the gardens of the sea with their corals.

03:17.160 --> 03:20.960
Here the fish swam like silver birds.

03:20.960 --> 03:32.240
She sang of the big whales from the cold north seas and of the dead sailors in their ships at the bottom of the sea.

03:32.240 --> 03:35.360
She sang of the little children.

03:35.360 --> 03:40.120
They ride on the backs of the dolphins and laugh.

03:40.120 --> 03:45.200
When she sang, the tuna fish came to listen to her.

03:45.200 --> 03:49.840
The young Fisherman then caught many of them.

03:49.840 --> 03:57.840
When his boat was full of fish, the mermaid smiled at him and swam away.

03:57.840 --> 04:00.920
But she never came near him.

04:00.920 --> 04:07.080
When he tried to catch her, she went into the water like a seal.

04:07.080 --> 04:11.560
Each day her voice became sweeter to his ears.

04:11.560 --> 04:16.840
Soon he forgot his nets and listened to her song.

04:16.840 --> 04:21.480
He listened to her until the moon came.

04:21.480 --> 04:25.320
One evening he called her and said,

04:25.320 --> 04:30.520
Little mermaid, marry me because I love you.

04:30.520 --> 04:33.480
But the little mermaid said,

04:33.480 --> 04:36.400
You have a human soul.

04:36.400 --> 04:42.480
Send away your soul and then I can love you.

04:42.480 --> 04:44.680
The young Fisherman thought,

04:44.680 --> 04:46.920
Why do I need my soul?

04:46.920 --> 04:48.440
I cannot see it.

04:48.440 --> 04:50.320
I cannot touch it.

04:50.320 --> 04:52.560
I do not know it.

04:52.560 --> 04:57.360
Of course, I will send it away and I will be very happy.

04:57.360 --> 05:00.520
He stood up in his boat and cried.

05:00.520 --> 05:03.960
I will send my soul away.

05:03.960 --> 05:10.640
You will be my wife and you will show me all the things you sing about.

05:10.640 --> 05:14.600
We will be together forever.

05:14.600 --> 05:19.960
The little mermaid laughed because she was very happy.

05:19.960 --> 05:23.000
But how can I send my soul away?

05:23.080 --> 05:25.320
The young Fisherman.

05:25.320 --> 05:29.920
I do not know, said the little mermaid.

05:29.920 --> 05:35.160
The people of the sea have no souls.

05:35.160 --> 05:37.280
Early the next morning,

05:37.280 --> 05:45.080
the Fisherman went to the priest's house and knocked on his door.

05:45.080 --> 05:51.520
The priest looked out of the window and saw the Fisherman and said,

05:51.520 --> 05:53.520
Come in.

05:53.520 --> 05:57.800
The young Fisherman entered and cried to the priest.

05:57.800 --> 06:01.440
Father, I am in love with a mermaid.

06:01.440 --> 06:05.760
I cannot marry her because I have a soul.

06:05.760 --> 06:08.720
How can I send my soul away?

06:08.720 --> 06:12.120
I really do not need it.

06:12.120 --> 06:15.160
Why is my soul important?

06:15.160 --> 06:17.120
I cannot see it.

06:17.120 --> 06:19.240
I cannot touch it.

06:19.280 --> 06:21.680
I do not know it.

06:21.680 --> 06:23.720
The priest answered,

06:23.720 --> 06:25.800
Are you mad?

06:25.800 --> 06:29.320
God gave you your soul.

06:29.320 --> 06:32.440
It is very precious.

06:32.440 --> 06:37.280
It is as precious as all the gold in the world.

06:37.280 --> 06:42.440
So, my son, do not think about this anymore.

06:42.440 --> 06:45.720
It is the worst sin.

06:45.720 --> 06:49.360
The people of the sea are lost creatures.

06:49.360 --> 06:52.840
They are like the beasts of the field.

06:52.840 --> 06:56.400
They do not know what is right and wrong.

06:56.400 --> 07:00.320
God didn't die for them.

07:00.320 --> 07:06.640
The young Fisherman began to cry and said,

07:06.640 --> 07:12.960
Father, the fawns live in the forest and are happy.

07:12.960 --> 07:17.400
The mermaids sit on the rocks with their gold harps.

07:17.400 --> 07:20.240
I want to be like them.

07:20.240 --> 07:22.760
Why is my soul important?

07:22.760 --> 07:26.840
I have a soul, but I cannot have the mermaid.

07:26.840 --> 07:28.440
And I love her.

07:28.440 --> 07:30.960
He cried.

07:30.960 --> 07:34.480
It is horrible to love your body.

07:34.480 --> 07:36.320
Cried the priest.

07:36.320 --> 07:41.080
The fawns of the woods and the mermaid are horrible.

07:41.160 --> 07:43.200
I hear them at night.

07:43.200 --> 07:46.880
They try to distract me from my prayers.

07:46.880 --> 07:48.640
They are lost, I tell you.

07:48.640 --> 07:50.200
They are lost.

07:50.200 --> 07:53.880
There is no heaven or hell for them.

07:53.880 --> 07:55.360
Away away!

07:55.360 --> 07:56.600
Cried the priest.

07:56.600 --> 08:00.640
Your mermaid is lost and you will be lost with her.

08:00.640 --> 08:06.000
The young Fisherman walked sadly to the marketplace.

08:06.000 --> 08:09.160
When the merchants saw him, they said,

08:09.160 --> 08:11.600
What do you want to sell?

08:11.600 --> 08:14.560
I will sell you my soul, he answered.

08:14.560 --> 08:19.040
Please buy it from me, because I am tired of it.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.760
What can I do with a soul?

08:21.760 --> 08:23.560
I cannot see it.

08:23.560 --> 08:25.400
I cannot touch it.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.840
I do not know it.

08:27.840 --> 08:32.480
But the merchants laughed at him and said,

08:32.480 --> 08:34.520
What can we do with a soul?

08:34.520 --> 08:37.400
A false coin is more precious.

08:37.400 --> 08:42.040
Sellers your body and we will give you a lot of gold.

08:42.040 --> 08:45.640
But we will not give you any money for your soul.

08:45.640 --> 08:50.320
The young Fisherman thought, How strange this is.

08:50.320 --> 08:56.800
The priest said, Your soul is as precious as all the gold in the world.

08:56.800 --> 09:02.000
But the merchants say, A false coin is more precious.

09:02.000 --> 09:09.840
He went to the beach and began to think.

09:09.840 --> 09:17.160
Chapter 2 The Witch At midday, he remembered that there was

09:17.160 --> 09:19.440
a young witch.

09:19.440 --> 09:24.160
She lived in a cave and she was very good at magic.

09:24.160 --> 09:26.560
He ran quickly to her.

09:26.560 --> 09:28.800
What do you need?

09:28.800 --> 09:30.480
What do you need?

09:30.480 --> 09:34.000
She cried when he ran towards her cave.

09:34.000 --> 09:37.800
Do you need fish when the weather is bad?

09:37.800 --> 09:40.600
I have a special instrument.

09:40.600 --> 09:45.240
You play it and all the fish swim into the bay.

09:45.240 --> 09:47.360
But it has a price.

09:47.360 --> 09:48.840
Pretty boy.

09:48.840 --> 09:52.280
It has a price.

09:52.280 --> 09:53.440
What do you need?

09:53.440 --> 09:54.680
What do you need?

09:54.680 --> 09:58.160
A storm to destroy the ships.

09:58.160 --> 10:01.480
Do you want the gold on the ships?

10:01.480 --> 10:03.440
I can help you.

10:03.440 --> 10:06.920
I have more storms than the wind.

10:06.920 --> 10:11.960
My master is stronger than the wind, but I have a price.

10:11.960 --> 10:13.360
Pretty boy.

10:13.360 --> 10:15.440
I have a price.

10:15.440 --> 10:17.520
I do not want very much.

10:17.520 --> 10:19.400
Said the young Fisherman.

10:19.400 --> 10:25.320
But the priest is very angry with me and the merchants laugh at me.

10:25.320 --> 10:30.800
So I came to you and I will pay you any price.

10:30.800 --> 10:33.120
What do you want?

10:33.120 --> 10:34.680
Asked the witch.

10:34.680 --> 10:38.080
I want to send my soul away from me.

10:38.080 --> 10:41.160
Answered the young Fisherman.

10:41.160 --> 10:44.040
The witch's face became white.

10:44.040 --> 10:49.920
Pretty boy, pretty boy, she said.

10:49.920 --> 10:53.840
That is a terrible thing to do.

10:53.840 --> 10:58.160
She laughed and answered her.

10:58.160 --> 11:01.360
My soul is not important to me.

11:01.360 --> 11:03.280
I cannot see it.

11:03.280 --> 11:05.280
I cannot touch it.

11:05.280 --> 11:08.240
I do not know it.

11:08.240 --> 11:13.920
I will tell you, but you must give me something.

11:13.920 --> 11:16.360
Said the witch.

11:16.360 --> 11:20.680
She looked at him with her beautiful eyes.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.640
Five pieces of gold.

11:22.640 --> 11:23.640
She said.

11:23.640 --> 11:25.040
And my nets.

11:25.040 --> 11:26.520
And my house.

11:26.520 --> 11:28.480
And my boat.

11:28.480 --> 11:31.280
But how can I send away my soul?

11:31.280 --> 11:34.200
She laughed and answered.

11:34.200 --> 11:38.440
I can change the autumn leaves into gold.

11:38.440 --> 11:43.080
I can change the light of the moon into silver.

11:43.080 --> 11:48.920
My master is richer than all the kings of this world.

11:49.000 --> 11:54.160
The witch caressed his hair with her thin white hand.

11:54.160 --> 11:58.440
You must dance with me, pretty boy.

11:58.440 --> 12:00.680
She said softly.

12:00.680 --> 12:03.160
And she smiled at him.

12:03.160 --> 12:04.520
Only this.

12:04.520 --> 12:07.000
Cried the young Fisherman.

12:07.000 --> 12:09.600
Only this.

12:09.600 --> 12:11.200
She answered.

12:11.200 --> 12:14.000
And she smiled at him again.

12:14.000 --> 12:18.760
Then we will dance together in a secret place at sunset.

12:19.440 --> 12:22.520
And you will tell me everything.

12:22.520 --> 12:26.040
Then I can send away my soul.

12:26.040 --> 12:28.880
When the moon is full.

12:28.880 --> 12:31.480
When the moon is full.

12:31.480 --> 12:33.880
She said softly.

12:33.880 --> 12:37.360
Then she looked around and listened.

12:37.360 --> 12:39.760
Three birds sang.

12:39.760 --> 12:42.640
There was no other sound.

12:42.640 --> 12:46.200
There was only the sound of the waves.

12:46.360 --> 12:49.120
So she pulled him next to her.

12:49.120 --> 12:53.680
She put her dry lips close to his ear.

12:53.680 --> 13:00.520
Tonight you must come to the top of the mountain, she whispered.

13:00.520 --> 13:03.040
It is a special night.

13:03.040 --> 13:05.560
And he will be there.

13:05.560 --> 13:07.880
Who is he?

13:07.880 --> 13:09.800
He asked.

13:09.800 --> 13:14.200
It is not important, she answered.

13:14.200 --> 13:18.240
Go tonight and stand under the tree.

13:18.240 --> 13:20.480
And wait for me.

13:20.480 --> 13:22.680
You will see a dog.

13:22.680 --> 13:26.080
And you must hit it with a stick.

13:26.080 --> 13:29.120
The dog will run away.

13:29.120 --> 13:33.840
Remember, do not speak to the owl.

13:33.840 --> 13:37.080
I will come with the full moon.

13:37.080 --> 13:40.520
And we will dance together.

13:40.520 --> 13:43.560
How can I send my soul away?

13:43.560 --> 13:45.800
You must promise to tell me.

13:45.800 --> 13:48.000
He said.

13:48.000 --> 13:52.360
She came out of the cave into the sun.

13:52.360 --> 13:54.280
I promise.

13:54.280 --> 13:56.160
She answered.

13:56.160 --> 13:59.080
You are the best witch in the world.

13:59.080 --> 14:00.960
Cried the fisherman.

14:00.960 --> 14:04.920
And he ran back to the town happily.

14:04.920 --> 14:10.320
The witch went into her cave and burned a magic plant.

14:10.320 --> 14:13.280
She looked into the smoke.

14:13.360 --> 14:16.960
After some time, she said angrily.

14:16.960 --> 14:19.040
He must be mine.

14:19.040 --> 14:22.880
I am as beautiful as she is.

14:22.880 --> 14:26.400
That evening, when the moon appeared,

14:26.400 --> 14:29.920
the fisherman went to the top of the mountain.

14:29.920 --> 14:32.800
He stood under the tree.

14:32.800 --> 14:36.920
A big owl with yellow eyes called his name.

14:36.920 --> 14:39.320
He did not answer.

14:39.320 --> 14:42.320
A black dog ran towards him.

14:42.320 --> 14:47.120
He hit it with a stick, and it ran away.

14:47.120 --> 14:50.840
At midnight, the witches were in the sky.

14:50.840 --> 14:53.000
They were like bats.

14:53.000 --> 14:54.760
Feel.

14:54.760 --> 14:57.920
They cried when they came to the ground.

14:57.920 --> 15:03.480
There is someone here, and we do not know him.

15:03.480 --> 15:07.840
Finally, the young witch with red hair appeared.

15:07.840 --> 15:11.720
She wore a gold dress with peacock's eyes on it,

15:11.720 --> 15:14.840
and her little hat was green.

15:14.840 --> 15:16.280
Where is he?

15:16.280 --> 15:18.360
Where is he?

15:18.360 --> 15:21.720
Asked the witches when they saw her.

15:21.720 --> 15:25.000
She laughed and ran to the fisherman.

15:25.000 --> 15:30.280
She took him by the hand, and then they danced in the moonlight.

15:30.280 --> 15:33.120
They danced round and round.

15:33.120 --> 15:36.960
Then they heard the sound of a galloping horse.

15:36.960 --> 15:39.400
But they did not see a horse.

15:39.400 --> 15:46.520
Faster, faster, she cried, and then the fisherman was afraid.

15:46.520 --> 15:51.960
Something very bad was there, and he was afraid of it.

15:51.960 --> 15:54.960
There was a man near a rock.

15:54.960 --> 15:58.480
He wore elegant Spanish clothes.

15:58.480 --> 16:02.720
This man watched the fisherman constantly.

16:02.720 --> 16:13.080
The witch laughed, and he danced with her round and round.

16:13.080 --> 16:24.160
Chapter 3 The Secret A dog barked, and the dancers stopped.

16:24.160 --> 16:28.280
They went to the man and kissed his hand.

16:29.280 --> 16:32.880
Come, let's pray.

16:32.880 --> 16:35.880
The witch said softly.

16:35.880 --> 16:40.440
The fisherman wanted to do this, and he followed her.

16:40.440 --> 16:45.880
But when he came near the man, he called God's name.

16:45.880 --> 16:51.920
When he did this, the witches screamed and went away.

16:51.920 --> 16:56.280
A horse came, and the man got on it.

16:56.360 --> 17:02.880
He looked at the fisherman, sadly, and then disappeared.

17:02.880 --> 17:10.000
The witch, with red hair, tried to fly away too, but the fisherman stopped her.

17:10.000 --> 17:12.040
Let me go!

17:12.040 --> 17:13.800
She cried.

17:13.800 --> 17:16.640
You must not say God's name.

17:16.640 --> 17:17.640
No.

17:17.640 --> 17:18.800
He answered.

17:18.800 --> 17:20.880
You are my prisoner.

17:20.880 --> 17:22.800
Tell me the secret now.

17:22.800 --> 17:24.800
What secret?

17:24.840 --> 17:26.520
The witch.

17:26.520 --> 17:28.440
She tried to escape.

17:28.440 --> 17:30.880
You know.

17:30.880 --> 17:33.400
He answered.

17:33.400 --> 17:41.880
She began to cry, and said to the fisherman, ask me anything, but not that.

17:41.880 --> 17:46.240
He laughed, and didn't want to release her.

17:46.240 --> 17:53.520
She could not escape, and so she said, I am as beautiful as the mermaids.

17:53.520 --> 18:00.760
Then she put her face near his, but he pushed her away and said, I will kill you.

18:00.760 --> 18:03.680
You must tell me the secret now.

18:03.680 --> 18:04.680
She trembled.

18:04.680 --> 18:07.160
All right.

18:07.160 --> 18:13.880
She said, it is your soul, not mine.

18:13.880 --> 18:17.200
She gave him a little knife.

18:17.200 --> 18:19.280
Why did you give me this knife?

18:19.280 --> 18:21.520
He asked.

18:21.520 --> 18:23.720
She was silent for a moment.

18:23.720 --> 18:25.760
She was terrified.

18:25.760 --> 18:32.520
Then she said to him, our shadow is not the shadow of our bodies.

18:32.520 --> 18:36.560
It is the body of our souls.

18:36.560 --> 18:40.320
Stand on the beach with your back to the moon.

18:40.320 --> 18:43.400
Cut your shadow from your feet.

18:43.400 --> 18:49.920
Then you must tell your soul to leave, and it will leave.

18:49.920 --> 18:52.440
The young fisherman trembled.

18:52.440 --> 18:53.760
Is this true?

18:53.760 --> 18:55.400
He said.

18:55.400 --> 18:59.160
He released her and took the knife.

18:59.160 --> 19:02.120
Then he walked to the sea.

19:02.120 --> 19:07.680
The fisherman's soul then said to him, I am your servant.

19:07.680 --> 19:10.960
Do not send me away now.

19:10.960 --> 19:14.280
Did I do anything bad to you?

19:14.280 --> 19:17.920
The young fisherman laughed.

19:17.920 --> 19:22.200
You didn't do anything bad, but I do not need you.

19:22.200 --> 19:23.200
He answered.

19:23.200 --> 19:25.000
The world is big.

19:25.000 --> 19:32.120
Go where you want, but do not disturb me, because my love is calling me.

19:32.120 --> 19:36.960
His soul called him many times, but he did not listen.

19:36.960 --> 19:42.880
He then arrived on the beach and stood on the sand with his back to the moon.

19:42.880 --> 19:48.440
Right arms came out of the foam, and they asked him to come.

19:48.440 --> 19:54.400
His soul said to him, do not send me away without a heart.

19:54.400 --> 19:57.440
The world is cruel.

19:57.440 --> 19:59.960
Give me your heart.

19:59.960 --> 20:03.200
How can I love my mermaid without a heart?

20:03.200 --> 20:04.360
He cried.

20:04.360 --> 20:05.840
Please.

20:05.840 --> 20:07.400
Said his soul.

20:07.400 --> 20:09.200
Give me your heart.

20:09.200 --> 20:13.520
The world is cruel, and I am afraid.

20:13.520 --> 20:16.120
My heart is with my love now.

20:16.120 --> 20:17.560
He answered.

20:17.560 --> 20:19.160
Go away.

20:19.160 --> 20:21.920
But I also need to love.

20:21.920 --> 20:23.320
Said his soul.

20:23.320 --> 20:24.720
Go away.

20:24.720 --> 20:26.640
I do not need you.

20:26.640 --> 20:28.720
Cried the young fisherman.

20:28.720 --> 20:33.320
He took the little knife and cut his shadow from his feet.

20:33.320 --> 20:39.320
The shadow stood up in front of him, and it was very similar to the fisherman.

20:39.320 --> 20:44.240
The fisherman moved back slowly, and he was afraid.

20:44.240 --> 20:45.240
Go away.

20:45.240 --> 20:46.240
He mermaid.

20:46.240 --> 20:48.760
And never come back again.

20:48.760 --> 20:51.840
No, but we must meet again.

20:51.840 --> 20:53.600
Said the soul.

20:53.600 --> 20:56.960
The soul's voice was like a flute.

20:56.960 --> 20:58.760
How will we meet?

20:58.760 --> 21:00.480
Cried the young fisherman.

21:00.480 --> 21:03.240
Will you follow me into the sea?

21:03.240 --> 21:08.240
Once every year I will come to this place and call you.

21:08.240 --> 21:09.920
Said the soul.

21:09.920 --> 21:12.960
Perhaps you will need me.

21:12.960 --> 21:14.960
I do not think I will need you.

21:14.960 --> 21:16.600
Cried the young fisherman.

21:16.600 --> 21:18.640
But you can call me.

21:18.640 --> 21:21.080
I can come here again.

21:21.080 --> 21:27.080
He went into the water, and the tritons played their musical instruments.

21:27.080 --> 21:30.240
The little mermaid came to meet him.

21:30.240 --> 21:35.400
She put her arms around his neck and kissed him on the mouth.

21:35.400 --> 21:40.000
The soul stood on the beach and watched them.

21:40.000 --> 21:52.160
And when they disappeared into the sea, the fisherman's soul walked away and cried.

21:52.160 --> 21:57.360
Chapter 4 The soul's first journey.

21:57.360 --> 22:02.960
After a year, the soul came down to the sea and called the young fisherman.

22:02.960 --> 22:07.400
He came out of the sea and said, Why do you call me?

22:07.400 --> 22:11.040
The soul answered, Come near her.

22:11.040 --> 22:15.880
I want to speak to you because I saw marvellous things.

22:15.880 --> 22:21.160
So he came nearer and sat in the water and listened.

22:21.160 --> 22:26.400
The soul said to him, When I left you, I went towards the east

22:26.400 --> 22:28.920
and traveled.

22:28.920 --> 22:32.520
Everything wise comes from the east.

22:32.520 --> 22:36.600
After six days, I came to the land of the Tatas.

22:36.600 --> 22:41.600
One night, I saw a fire and a camp of a company of merchants.

22:41.600 --> 22:46.360
I went to them, and the chief of merchants stood up and took his sword.

22:46.360 --> 22:48.160
Who are you?

22:48.160 --> 22:49.160
He asked.

22:49.960 --> 22:56.440
I am a prince, and I escaped from the Tatas, I replied.

22:56.440 --> 23:01.880
He lowered his head as a sign of respect and took my hand.

23:01.880 --> 23:07.920
Then we left the country of the Tatas, and we traveled in many strange lands and saw

23:07.920 --> 23:11.040
many strange people.

23:11.040 --> 23:15.120
I traveled on a camel next to the chief.

23:15.120 --> 23:21.560
There were forty camels in the caravan and eighty mules.

23:21.560 --> 23:25.760
During our journey, we battled with the tribe of the Magadie.

23:25.760 --> 23:33.320
They are born old and grow younger every year and die when they are little children.

23:33.320 --> 23:35.840
We battled with the Lactroy.

23:35.840 --> 23:42.160
They think they are the sons of tigers, and they paint their bodies yellow and black.

23:42.160 --> 23:45.160
They also battled with the Sibians.

23:45.160 --> 23:51.760
They have horses feet, and they run quicker than horses.

23:51.760 --> 23:56.480
In the fourth month, we arrived in the city of Ilelle.

23:56.480 --> 24:00.880
It was night, and we waited for day to come.

24:00.880 --> 24:05.080
That morning, we knocked at the gate of the city.

24:05.080 --> 24:12.120
The gate was of red bronze, and it had images of sea dragons and dragons with wings.

24:12.120 --> 24:18.320
A guard then said to us, what do you want?

24:18.320 --> 24:24.280
We are from the island of Syria, and we have a lot of merchandise to sell, we answered.

24:24.280 --> 24:27.200
Then wait here until midday.

24:27.200 --> 24:36.640
He said, at midday they opened the gates, and we went to the marketplace.

24:36.640 --> 24:41.480
After a month in the city of Ilelle, I became tired of it.

24:41.480 --> 24:47.840
I walked in the streets of the city, and came to the garden of the God of the city.

24:47.840 --> 24:53.600
The priests and their yellow tunics walked silently in the garden.

24:53.600 --> 24:56.080
There was a red house.

24:56.080 --> 24:58.760
This was the home of the God.

24:58.760 --> 25:05.120
The doors had images of golden animals and peacocks on them.

25:05.120 --> 25:09.400
There was a pool of clear water in front of the temple.

25:09.400 --> 25:12.080
I sat down near it.

25:12.080 --> 25:16.000
One of the priests came to me and stood behind me.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.520
What do you want?

25:18.520 --> 25:20.640
He asked me.

25:20.640 --> 25:25.240
I want to see the God, I replied.

25:25.240 --> 25:32.560
The God is hunting in a forest, said the priest, and he looked at me strangely.

25:32.560 --> 25:35.200
Which forest is he in?

25:35.200 --> 25:40.040
Tell me, and I will go there, I answered.

25:40.040 --> 25:43.600
He moved his hands on his soft tunic.

25:43.600 --> 25:47.680
The God is asleep, he murmured.

25:47.680 --> 25:49.520
Which bed is he in?

25:49.520 --> 25:53.480
Tell me, and I will stand near him, I answered.

25:53.480 --> 25:56.440
The God is at the feast, he cried.

25:56.440 --> 26:02.080
I will drink bitter or sweet wine with him, I said.

26:02.080 --> 26:07.000
He was surprised and accompanied me into the temple.

26:07.000 --> 26:14.720
In the first room I saw an ebony idol on a throne, and it was the size of a man.

26:14.720 --> 26:17.640
There was a ruby on its forehead.

26:17.640 --> 26:22.560
Its feet were red from the blood of a baby goat.

26:22.560 --> 26:27.760
I said to the priest, is this the God?

26:27.760 --> 26:31.760
This is the God, he answered.

26:31.760 --> 26:39.400
This is not the God, show me the God, I cried, or I will kill you.

26:39.400 --> 26:44.360
I touched his hand, and it became small and dry.

26:44.360 --> 26:49.680
Make my hand better, and I will show you the God, he cried.

26:49.680 --> 26:54.440
So I breathed on his hand, and it became better.

26:54.440 --> 26:59.280
He trembled, and accompanied me into the second room.

26:59.280 --> 27:06.280
I saw an ivory idol on a lotus of jade with great emeralds on it.

27:06.280 --> 27:11.320
This idol was twice as big as a man.

27:11.320 --> 27:13.160
Is this the God?

27:13.160 --> 27:14.960
I asked him.

27:14.960 --> 27:18.960
This is the God, he replied.

27:18.960 --> 27:26.040
This is not the God, show me the God, I cried, or I will kill you.

27:26.040 --> 27:29.960
I touched his eyes, and they became blind.

27:29.960 --> 27:37.880
Please make my eyes better, then I will show you the God, he cried.

27:37.880 --> 27:42.320
So I breathed on his eyes, and they could see again.

27:42.320 --> 27:48.040
The priest trembled, and accompanied me into the third room.

27:48.040 --> 27:53.680
There was not an idol in it, only a mirror.

27:53.680 --> 27:58.680
I said to the priest, where is the God?

27:58.680 --> 28:05.960
He answered me, there is no God, but this is the mirror of wisdom.

28:05.960 --> 28:12.600
It reflects all the things in heaven and on earth, but it does not reflect the face of

28:12.600 --> 28:15.800
the person if they look into it.

28:15.800 --> 28:20.120
So this person can become wise.

28:20.120 --> 28:25.400
There are many other mirrors, but they are mirrors of opinion.

28:25.400 --> 28:29.740
This is the only mirror of wisdom.

28:29.740 --> 28:34.120
When you possess this mirror, you know everything.

28:34.120 --> 28:40.680
So it is a God, and we pray to this God.

28:40.680 --> 28:47.680
I looked into the mirror, the priest didn't lie.

28:47.680 --> 28:52.200
Then I did something strange, but it is not important.

28:52.200 --> 28:56.040
I placed the mirror in a valley near here.

28:56.040 --> 28:59.480
We can walk there in three days.

28:59.480 --> 29:05.320
Let me enter you again and be your servant, and you will have wisdom.

29:05.320 --> 29:09.400
But the young fisherman laughed.

29:09.400 --> 29:11.520
Love is better than wisdom.

29:11.520 --> 29:15.040
He cried, and the little mermaid loves me.

29:15.040 --> 29:18.960
Oh, there is nothing better than wisdom.

29:18.960 --> 29:20.920
Said the soul.

29:20.920 --> 29:22.680
Love is better.

29:22.680 --> 29:24.640
Answered the young fisherman.

29:24.640 --> 29:34.160
He went back to the sea, and the soul walked away and cried.

29:34.160 --> 29:42.280
Chapter 5 The Ring of Ritches After the second year, the soul came down

29:42.280 --> 29:46.080
to the sea and called the young fisherman.

29:46.080 --> 29:50.000
He came out of the sea and said, Why do you call me?

29:50.000 --> 29:53.560
The soul answered, Come near her.

29:53.560 --> 29:58.840
I want to speak to you, because I saw marvellous things.

29:58.840 --> 30:04.760
So he came nearer and sat in the water and listened.

30:04.760 --> 30:10.680
The soul said to him, When I left you, I went towards the south

30:10.680 --> 30:13.080
and traveled.

30:13.080 --> 30:17.560
Everything precious comes from the south.

30:17.560 --> 30:21.600
I traveled six days to the city of Ashta.

30:21.600 --> 30:26.640
I saw the city on the morning of the seventh day.

30:26.640 --> 30:28.760
The city is like a bazaar.

30:28.760 --> 30:30.720
It is wonderful.

30:30.720 --> 30:34.280
Merchants sit on silk carpets.

30:34.280 --> 30:40.480
Some of them sell strange perfumes from the islands of the Indian sea, and the oil

30:40.480 --> 30:43.280
of red roses.

30:43.280 --> 30:50.520
Other merchants sell fantastic jewelry with tiger claws in gold, and leopard claws in

30:50.520 --> 30:53.240
gold also.

30:53.240 --> 31:01.720
The people sell all kinds of fruit, purple figs, yellow melons, white grapes, red gold

31:01.720 --> 31:06.920
oranges, and oval lemons of green gold.

31:06.920 --> 31:08.920
I saw an elephant.

31:08.920 --> 31:14.240
It stopped and began eating the oranges, and the people laughed.

31:14.240 --> 31:18.200
You cannot imagine how strange these people are.

31:18.200 --> 31:22.000
When they are happy, they buy a bird in a cage.

31:22.000 --> 31:26.960
Then they release the bird, because they want to be happier.

31:26.960 --> 31:34.600
When they are sad, they hit their bodies with thorns, because they want to be sadder.

31:34.600 --> 31:39.840
On the feast of the new moon, the emperor came out of his palace and went into the

31:39.840 --> 31:42.400
mosque to pray.

31:42.400 --> 31:48.600
The people covered their faces, but I showed him no form of respect.

31:48.600 --> 31:52.680
That night, the guards of the emperor came for me.

31:52.680 --> 31:55.640
They accompanied me into the palace.

31:55.640 --> 32:01.240
We walked across a great court, and then we entered a beautiful garden.

32:01.240 --> 32:05.360
At the end of the garden, there was a pavilion.

32:05.360 --> 32:09.840
Then the captain of the guard told me to enter.

32:09.840 --> 32:16.760
The young emperor was there on a bed of lion skins, and he held a falcon.

32:16.760 --> 32:19.640
A newbian stood behind him.

32:19.640 --> 32:26.160
A large scimitar of steel was on a table next to the bed.

32:26.160 --> 32:29.960
When the emperor saw me, he was worried and said to me,

32:29.960 --> 32:31.520
what is your name?

32:31.520 --> 32:35.560
Don't you know that I am emperor of this city?

32:35.560 --> 32:38.360
I did not answer him.

32:38.360 --> 32:46.320
He indicated the scimitar, and the newbian took it and hit me with great violence.

32:46.320 --> 32:48.840
It did not hurt me.

32:48.840 --> 32:53.240
The newbian was terrified and went away.

32:53.240 --> 32:58.080
The emperor tried to kill me with a lance, but he didn't hurt me.

32:58.080 --> 33:03.760
He tried to kill me with an arrow, but I stopped it in the air.

33:03.760 --> 33:07.280
Then the emperor said to me, why can't I hurt you?

33:07.280 --> 33:11.520
Are you a prophet or the son of a prophet?

33:11.520 --> 33:14.360
Please leave my city tonight.

33:14.360 --> 33:18.520
You are here now, and I am not its lord.

33:18.520 --> 33:20.240
I answered him.

33:20.240 --> 33:22.560
Give me half of your treasure.

33:22.560 --> 33:25.800
Then I will go away.

33:25.800 --> 33:31.520
So he took my hand and accompanied me to a large room.

33:31.520 --> 33:35.000
He touched one of the walls and it opened.

33:35.000 --> 33:38.080
Then we walked down a corridor.

33:38.080 --> 33:43.320
He said a magic word and a granite door opened.

33:43.320 --> 33:49.120
The emperor covered his eyes with his hands to protect them from the light of the jewels

33:49.120 --> 33:50.880
there.

33:50.880 --> 33:53.920
It was really marvellous inside.

33:53.920 --> 34:02.080
There were huge tortoise shells full of pearls and many other wonderful jewels.

34:02.080 --> 34:09.480
Then the emperor said to me, this is my house of treasure and half of it is yours, but you

34:09.480 --> 34:11.480
must go tonight.

34:11.480 --> 34:14.800
My father, the son, must not see this.

34:14.800 --> 34:18.200
I cannot kill a man in the city.

34:18.200 --> 34:20.280
I answered him.

34:20.280 --> 34:24.680
The gold and all the precious jewels are yours.

34:24.680 --> 34:29.680
I only want your little ring.

34:29.680 --> 34:31.760
The emperor frowned.

34:31.760 --> 34:36.800
It is only a ring of lead, he cried, and it has no value.

34:36.800 --> 34:40.680
Take your half of the treasure and go away from my city.

34:40.680 --> 34:43.120
No, I answered.

34:43.120 --> 34:49.600
I know that it is really the ring of riches.

34:49.600 --> 34:54.640
The emperor trembled and said, take all the treasure and go from my city.

34:54.640 --> 34:58.160
You can also have my half of the treasure.

34:58.160 --> 35:03.200
Then I did something strange, but it is not important.

35:03.200 --> 35:08.640
What is important is that I put the ring of riches in a cave.

35:08.640 --> 35:12.200
You can arrive there in one day.

35:12.200 --> 35:17.760
The owner of this ring is richer than all the kings of the world.

35:17.760 --> 35:22.360
But the young fisherman laughed.

35:22.360 --> 35:24.240
Love is better than riches.

35:24.240 --> 35:25.480
He cried.

35:25.480 --> 35:28.240
And the little mermaid loves me.

35:28.240 --> 35:31.840
No, nothing is better than riches.

35:31.840 --> 35:33.880
Said the soul.

35:33.880 --> 35:36.000
Love is better.

35:36.000 --> 35:39.240
answered the young fisherman.

35:39.240 --> 35:44.720
He went back to the sea and the soul walked away and cried.

35:48.760 --> 35:54.760
Chapter 6 The soul's Third Journey

35:54.760 --> 36:00.760
After the third year, the soul came down to the sea and called the young fisherman.

36:00.760 --> 36:04.760
He came out of the sea and said, why do you call me?

36:04.760 --> 36:08.760
The soul answered, come nearer.

36:08.760 --> 36:13.760
I want to speak to you because I saw marvellous things.

36:14.760 --> 36:19.760
So he came nearer and sat in the water and listened.

36:19.760 --> 36:25.760
The soul said to him, I went to an inn near a river in a city.

36:25.760 --> 36:30.760
I sat with sailors and they ordered food and drink.

36:30.760 --> 36:36.760
After some time, an old man entered with a carpet and a loot.

36:36.760 --> 36:39.760
He put the carpet on the floor.

36:39.760 --> 36:45.760
When he played the loot, a girl came in and began to dance.

36:45.760 --> 36:50.760
There was a veil on her face and she had no shoes.

36:50.760 --> 36:55.760
Her feet moved on the carpet like little white pigeons.

36:55.760 --> 37:00.760
It was really marvellous and it is only one day away from here.

37:00.760 --> 37:03.760
The young fisherman heard these words.

37:03.760 --> 37:08.760
He remembered that the little mermaid had no feet and could not dance.

37:08.760 --> 37:14.760
He thought, it is only one day away and I can return to my love.

37:14.760 --> 37:19.760
He laughed, stood up in the water and walked towards the beach.

37:19.760 --> 37:25.760
When he reached the beach, his soul ran towards him and entered him.

37:25.760 --> 37:32.760
Then the young fisherman saw on the sand the shadow of the body, the body of the soul.

37:32.760 --> 37:38.760
They began their journey and the next evening they came to a city.

37:38.760 --> 37:43.760
The young fisherman said to his soul, does she dance in this city?

37:43.760 --> 37:48.760
His soul answered him, not in this city but another.

37:48.760 --> 37:51.760
Let's enter this city anyway.

37:51.760 --> 37:54.760
So they entered and walked in the streets.

37:54.760 --> 38:00.760
The young fisherman saw a silver cup on a stall in the street of the jewelers.

38:00.760 --> 38:05.760
His soul said to him, take that silver cup and hide it.

38:05.760 --> 38:11.760
So he took the silver cup and hid it and they went quickly out of the city.

38:11.760 --> 38:17.760
When they were far from the city, the young fisherman threw the cup away.

38:17.760 --> 38:22.760
He said to his soul, it was not a good thing to take the cup and hide it.

38:22.760 --> 38:27.760
But his soul answered him, calm down, calm down.

38:27.760 --> 38:31.760
On the evening of the second day, they came to a city.

38:31.760 --> 38:37.760
The young fisherman said to his soul, does she dance in this city?

38:37.760 --> 38:42.760
His soul answered him, not in this city but in another.

38:42.760 --> 38:45.760
Let's enter this city anyway.

38:45.760 --> 38:48.760
So they entered and walked in the streets.

38:48.760 --> 38:54.760
In the street of the cellars of sandals, the young fisherman saw a child.

38:54.760 --> 38:56.760
His soul said to him, hit that child.

38:56.760 --> 39:03.760
So he hit the child and the child cried and then they went quickly out of the city.

39:03.760 --> 39:10.760
When they were far from the city, the young fisherman became angry and said to his soul,

39:10.760 --> 39:13.760
it was not a good thing to hit the child.

39:13.760 --> 39:18.760
But his soul answered him, calm down, calm down.

39:18.760 --> 39:23.760
On the evening of the third day, they came to a city.

39:23.760 --> 39:28.760
The young fisherman said to his soul, does she dance in this city?

39:28.760 --> 39:33.760
His soul answered him, perhaps this is the city.

39:33.760 --> 39:35.760
Let's enter.

39:35.760 --> 39:41.760
They walked in the streets, but the young fisherman could not find the inn near the river.

39:41.760 --> 39:47.760
He wanted to leave, but his soul said to him, let's stay here tonight.

39:47.760 --> 39:50.760
Perhaps there are robbers outside.

39:50.760 --> 39:54.760
So the fisherman sat down in the marketplace.

39:54.760 --> 40:00.760
After some time, a merchant came and said to him, why are you here?

40:00.760 --> 40:02.760
The market is closed.

40:02.760 --> 40:07.760
The young fisherman answered him, I can't find an inn in this city.

40:07.760 --> 40:11.760
I have no family here and I need a room for the night.

40:11.760 --> 40:14.760
We are all of the same family.

40:14.760 --> 40:15.760
Said the merchant.

40:15.760 --> 40:17.760
And one God made us.

40:17.760 --> 40:19.760
Come with me.

40:19.760 --> 40:21.760
I have a room.

40:21.760 --> 40:24.760
The young fisherman followed the merchant to his house.

40:24.760 --> 40:28.760
The merchant gave him good food and a comfortable room.

40:28.760 --> 40:31.760
The young fisherman then went to sleep.

40:31.760 --> 40:42.760
After three hours, his soul woke him and said, go to the room of the merchant and kill him and take his gold.

40:42.760 --> 40:46.760
The young fisherman went into the merchant's room.

40:46.760 --> 40:52.760
There was a sword near his feet and nine purses of gold next to the bed.

40:52.760 --> 40:59.760
When he touched the sword, the merchant woke up and said, why do you want to kill me?

40:59.760 --> 41:04.760
I gave you good food and a room. I was kind to you.

41:04.760 --> 41:08.760
His soul said to the young fisherman, hit him.

41:08.760 --> 41:12.760
So he hit him and the merchant lost consciousness.

41:12.760 --> 41:18.760
He then took the nine purses of gold and went quickly away from the city.

41:18.760 --> 41:23.760
When they were far from the city, the young fisherman said to his soul.

41:23.760 --> 41:26.760
It was bad to hit the merchant and take his gold.

41:26.760 --> 41:28.760
But his soul answered him.

41:28.760 --> 41:30.760
Calm down.

41:30.760 --> 41:31.760
Calm down.

41:31.760 --> 41:32.760
No!

41:32.760 --> 41:34.760
Cried the young fisherman.

41:34.760 --> 41:36.760
I cannot be calm.

41:36.760 --> 41:40.760
You told me to do bad things and I hate these things.

41:40.760 --> 41:44.760
I also hate you. Why did you do these things?

41:44.760 --> 41:46.760
His soul answered him.

41:46.760 --> 41:52.760
When you sent me out into the world, you did not give me a heart.

41:52.760 --> 41:56.760
So I learned to do all these things and love them.

41:56.760 --> 41:58.760
What are you saying?

41:58.760 --> 42:00.760
Mermaid the young fisherman.

42:00.760 --> 42:01.760
You know.

42:01.760 --> 42:03.760
Answer his soul.

42:03.760 --> 42:06.760
You did not give me a heart.

42:06.760 --> 42:08.760
So stay calm.

42:08.760 --> 42:12.760
You will give other people all kinds of pain.

42:12.760 --> 42:16.760
And you will receive all kinds of pleasure.

42:16.760 --> 42:19.760
The young fisherman said to his soul, no.

42:19.760 --> 42:21.760
You are bad.

42:21.760 --> 42:26.760
And I forgot about my love and did many bad things because of you.

42:26.760 --> 42:28.760
His soul answered him.

42:28.760 --> 42:32.760
You did not forget that you sent me away without a heart.

42:32.760 --> 42:36.760
Let's go to another city and enjoy life together.

42:37.760 --> 42:40.760
We have nine purses of gold.

42:40.760 --> 42:46.760
But the young fisherman took the nine purses of gold and threw them on the ground.

42:46.760 --> 42:50.760
No! I will not come with you and I will send you away again.

42:50.760 --> 42:52.760
Said the young fisherman.

42:52.760 --> 42:54.760
He turned his back to the moon.

42:54.760 --> 43:00.760
With the little knife he tried to cut his shadow from his feet to eliminate his soul.

43:00.760 --> 43:04.760
But his soul did not leave him and said to him.

43:04.760 --> 43:07.760
The magic of the witch will not work.

43:07.760 --> 43:12.760
It only works once in a man's life.

43:12.760 --> 43:15.760
I will stay with you forever.

43:15.760 --> 43:19.760
And this is your punishment and your recompense.

43:19.760 --> 43:26.760
Now the young fisherman was desperate and cried because his soul was very bad.

43:26.760 --> 43:30.760
When it was day, the young fisherman said to his soul,

43:30.760 --> 43:33.760
I will tie my hands together.

43:33.760 --> 43:36.760
Then I cannot do what you tell me to do.

43:36.760 --> 43:41.760
I will return to the bay because my love sings there.

43:41.760 --> 43:43.760
I will call her.

43:43.760 --> 43:49.760
I will tell her about the bad things I did and the bad things you did to me.

43:49.760 --> 43:54.760
When he arrived on the beach, he freed his hands and called the mermaid.

43:54.760 --> 43:57.760
But she did not come.

43:57.760 --> 44:00.760
Your soul laughed at him and said.

44:00.760 --> 44:04.760
Your love gives you little joy.

44:04.760 --> 44:07.760
Come with me to the valley of pleasure.

44:07.760 --> 44:09.760
That is better for you.

44:09.760 --> 44:13.760
The young fisherman did not answer his soul.

44:13.760 --> 44:18.760
He built a house by the bay and lived there for a year.

44:18.760 --> 44:21.760
Every morning he called the mermaid.

44:21.760 --> 44:24.760
And every midday he called her again.

44:24.760 --> 44:27.760
And at night he spoke her name.

44:27.760 --> 44:30.760
But she never came to see him.

44:30.760 --> 44:33.760
And he did not see her anywhere.

44:33.760 --> 44:37.760
His soul always asked him to do bad things.

44:37.760 --> 44:50.760
But the young fisherman never listened to him because the power of his love was so great.

44:51.760 --> 44:55.760
After another year, the soul thought.

44:55.760 --> 45:00.760
I tempted him with bad and his love is stronger than I am.

45:00.760 --> 45:05.760
I will now tempt him with good and perhaps he will come with me.

45:05.760 --> 45:10.760
So he spoke to the young fisherman and said.

45:10.760 --> 45:15.760
I told you about the joy of the world and you did not listen to me.

45:15.760 --> 45:20.760
Now I will tell you about the pain in the world and maybe you will listen.

45:20.760 --> 45:25.760
Pain is the lord of this world and nobody can escape it.

45:25.760 --> 45:32.760
Some people do not have clothes and other people do not have food and others are ill.

45:32.760 --> 45:37.760
Come, let's go and help these people.

45:37.760 --> 45:40.760
Why do you wait here for your love?

45:40.760 --> 45:42.760
What is love?

45:42.760 --> 45:44.760
What is love?

45:44.760 --> 45:47.760
Why do you think it is so important?

45:47.760 --> 45:50.760
But the young fisherman did not answer.

45:50.760 --> 45:53.760
The power of his love was so great.

45:53.760 --> 45:59.760
Every morning he called the mermaid and every midday he called her again.

45:59.760 --> 46:02.760
And at night he spoke her name.

46:02.760 --> 46:05.760
But she never came to see him.

46:05.760 --> 46:08.760
And he did not see her anywhere.

46:09.760 --> 46:13.760
After the second year the soul said to the fisherman.

46:13.760 --> 46:21.760
I tempted you with bad and I tempted you with good and your love is stronger than I am.

46:21.760 --> 46:24.760
So I will not tempt you anymore.

46:24.760 --> 46:28.760
But can I please enter your heart and be with you again?

46:28.760 --> 46:30.760
Of course you can enter.

46:30.760 --> 46:32.760
Said the young fisherman.

46:32.760 --> 46:36.760
I am sure you suffered when you did not have a heart.

46:36.760 --> 46:42.760
But I can find no place to enter because there is love all around your heart.

46:42.760 --> 46:44.760
There is no space for me.

46:44.760 --> 46:46.760
Cried the soul.

46:46.760 --> 46:48.760
I am very sorry.

46:48.760 --> 46:51.760
Said the young fisherman.

46:51.760 --> 46:57.760
Just then he heard a terrible cry of sadness from the sea.

47:02.760 --> 47:05.760
The young fisherman ran to the beach.

47:05.760 --> 47:08.760
The black waves came quickly to the beach.

47:08.760 --> 47:12.760
They carried something that was whiter than silver.

47:12.760 --> 47:19.760
There at his feet the young fisherman saw the dead body of the little mermaid.

47:19.760 --> 47:25.760
He sat down next to her and he kissed her cold red mouth.

47:25.760 --> 47:31.760
He told the dead mermaid about his soul and all the bad things.

47:31.760 --> 47:39.760
He put her little hands around his neck and he touched her neck with his fingers.

47:39.760 --> 47:46.760
His joy was bitter and his pain was full of strange happiness.

47:46.760 --> 47:52.760
The black sea came nearer and nearer to them.

47:52.760 --> 47:54.760
Run away.

47:54.760 --> 47:55.760
Said his soul.

47:55.760 --> 47:58.760
The sea is coming closer and closer.

47:58.760 --> 48:00.760
Go away.

48:00.760 --> 48:02.760
It will kill you.

48:02.760 --> 48:04.760
Run away to a safe place.

48:04.760 --> 48:08.760
But please do not send me into another world without a heart.

48:08.760 --> 48:12.760
But the young fisherman did not listen to his soul.

48:12.760 --> 48:15.760
He said to the little mermaid.

48:15.760 --> 48:25.760
Love is better than wisdom and more precious than riches and more beautiful than the feet of the daughters of men.

48:25.760 --> 48:29.760
I called you in the morning but you did not come.

48:29.760 --> 48:35.760
The moon heard your name but you did not listen to me.

48:35.760 --> 48:48.760
I was bad when I abandoned you but your love was always with me and it was always stronger than bad and good.

48:48.760 --> 48:54.760
And now that you are dead I will die with you also.

48:54.760 --> 49:03.760
His soul implored him to leave but his love was too great and he did not listen to his soul.

49:03.760 --> 49:08.760
The sea came near and tried to cover him with its waves.

49:08.760 --> 49:17.760
When he knew that the end was near the young fisherman kissed the cold lips of the mermaid and his heart broke.

49:17.760 --> 49:21.760
It broke because it was so full of love.

49:21.760 --> 49:30.760
Then the soul finally entered his heart and the sea covered the young fisherman with its waves.

49:30.760 --> 49:42.760
Chapter 8. The Field of the Fullers

49:42.760 --> 49:45.760
In the morning the priest said,

49:45.760 --> 49:51.760
I will go and bless the sea because it was not calm last night.

49:51.760 --> 49:56.760
Monks, musicians and many other people went with him.

49:56.760 --> 50:01.760
When the priest reached the beach he saw the young fisherman.

50:01.760 --> 50:07.760
He was dead in the water and the body of the little mermaid was in his arms.

50:07.760 --> 50:10.760
The priest frowned and said,

50:10.760 --> 50:16.760
I will not bless the sea or anything in the sea.

50:16.760 --> 50:25.760
The young fisherman abandoned God for love and the punishment of God killed him and his love.

50:25.760 --> 50:35.760
Now take his body and the body of the mermaid and bury them in the corner of the field of the fullers.

50:35.760 --> 50:38.760
Do not put any sign there.

50:38.760 --> 50:45.760
The people put the dead bodies in a deep hole in the corner of the field of the fullers.

50:45.760 --> 50:48.760
They covered the hole with earth.

50:48.760 --> 50:51.760
No sweet herbs grew there.

50:52.760 --> 51:01.760
Three years later on a holy day the priest went to the chapel to speak to the people about the anger of God.

51:01.760 --> 51:07.760
When he went to the altar he saw that there were strange flowers on the altar.

51:07.760 --> 51:13.760
Their strange beauty worried him and their perfume was sweet.

51:13.760 --> 51:20.760
He was particularly happy and he did not understand why he was so happy.

51:20.760 --> 51:24.760
He wanted to speak to them about the anger of God.

51:24.760 --> 51:31.760
But the beauty of the white flowers worried him and their perfume was sweet.

51:31.760 --> 51:34.760
He did not speak of the anger of God.

51:34.760 --> 51:41.760
He spoke of the love of God and he did not know why he spoke like this.

51:41.760 --> 51:48.760
When he finished speaking the people cried and his eyes were full of tears.

51:48.760 --> 51:53.760
He was in a dream and he said to his deacons,

51:53.760 --> 51:56.760
What are the flowers on the altar?

51:56.760 --> 51:58.760
Where do they come from?

51:58.760 --> 52:00.760
They answered him.

52:00.760 --> 52:07.760
We do not know what kind of flowers they are but they come from the corner of the field of the fullers.

52:07.760 --> 52:13.760
The priest trembled and returned to his house and prayed.

52:13.760 --> 52:20.760
Early the next morning he left his house with monks, musicians and many other people.

52:20.760 --> 52:28.760
He walked to the beach and blessed the sea and all the wild things in it.

52:28.760 --> 52:33.760
He also blessed the fawns and the little things that danced in the forest.

52:33.760 --> 52:40.760
He blessed all things in the world of God and the people were full of joy.

52:40.760 --> 52:50.760
The people of the sea went to another part of the sea and they never came back again.

52:50.760 --> 52:53.760
The little mermaid.

52:53.760 --> 52:57.760
The king of the sea had six daughters.

52:57.760 --> 53:02.760
The youngest daughter had a beautiful underwater garden.

53:02.760 --> 53:06.760
In the garden there was a marble statue.

53:06.760 --> 53:12.760
It was the statue of a handsome prince and she loved it.

53:12.760 --> 53:16.760
One day their grandmother said to the six mermaids,

53:16.760 --> 53:24.760
When you are fifteen years old you can go to the surface and see the world of the mortals.

53:24.760 --> 53:29.760
The youngest mermaid wanted to be fifteen very much.

53:29.760 --> 53:35.760
Finally her fifteenth birthday came and she went to the surface.

53:35.760 --> 53:38.760
She saw a beautiful ship.

53:38.760 --> 53:43.760
There was a birthday party on the ship for a handsome prince.

53:43.760 --> 53:49.760
But a great storm came and broke the ship into many pieces.

53:49.760 --> 53:53.760
The prince fell into the water.

53:53.760 --> 54:03.760
At first the mermaid was very happy but then she remembered that human beings could not live under water.

54:03.760 --> 54:07.760
She took him to the beach and left him there.

54:07.760 --> 54:12.760
He did not know that the little mermaid saved his life.

54:12.760 --> 54:15.760
She returned to her home.

54:15.760 --> 54:21.760
She was only happy when she put her arms around the statue in her garden

54:21.760 --> 54:25.760
and when she swam near the prince's castle by the sea.

54:25.760 --> 54:30.760
One day she asked her grandmother about humans.

54:30.760 --> 54:32.760
Her grandmother said,

54:32.760 --> 54:40.760
We live for three hundred years but when we die we dissolve in the water and disappear.

54:40.760 --> 54:47.760
Humans do not live very long but they have an immortal soul that lives forever.

54:47.760 --> 54:49.760
I want to be like them!

54:49.760 --> 54:52.760
Cried the little mermaid.

54:52.760 --> 54:57.760
When a human loves you you can have an immortal soul.

54:57.760 --> 54:59.760
But that is impossible.

54:59.760 --> 55:03.760
We have tales and they are very beautiful.

55:03.760 --> 55:07.760
But humans think they are ugly.

55:07.760 --> 55:15.760
Humans have two ugly things called legs and they think they are beautiful.

55:15.760 --> 55:19.760
The little mermaid decided to go to the sea witch for help.

55:19.760 --> 55:21.760
The sea witch said,

55:21.760 --> 55:24.760
I know why you are here.

55:24.760 --> 55:27.760
I will give you a magic drink.

55:27.760 --> 55:34.760
You must drink it and your tail will divide in two and you will have legs.

55:34.760 --> 55:37.760
But you must pay me.

55:37.760 --> 55:41.760
You must give me your beautiful voice.

55:41.760 --> 55:45.760
Remember the prince must marry you.

55:45.760 --> 55:53.760
If he marries another you will dissolve in the water and disappear.

55:53.760 --> 55:58.760
The little mermaid drank the magic drink and then she had legs.

55:58.760 --> 56:02.760
The prince saw her and took her into his castle.

56:02.760 --> 56:07.760
He liked her very much but he did not want to marry her.

56:07.760 --> 56:12.760
In fact after some time he married a human princess.

56:12.760 --> 56:16.760
On the evening of the wedding the mermaid thought,

56:16.760 --> 56:21.760
Tomorrow when the sun comes up I will dissolve in the water.

56:21.760 --> 56:24.760
I will disappear.

56:24.760 --> 56:28.760
But the mermaid sisters had a knife from the sea witch.

56:28.760 --> 56:29.760
They said,

56:29.760 --> 56:34.760
Kill the prince with this knife and then you will have your tail again.

56:34.760 --> 56:39.760
You will live with us under the water for three hundred years.

56:39.760 --> 56:44.760
When the little mermaid saw the prince she did not want to kill him

56:44.760 --> 56:47.760
and she threw the knife into the sea.

56:47.760 --> 56:53.760
Just then the sun appeared in the sky but she did not disappear.

56:53.760 --> 57:00.760
No she went up into the sky and she heard beautiful voices.

57:00.760 --> 57:04.760
They were the voices of the daughters of the air.

57:04.760 --> 57:06.760
They said to her,

57:06.760 --> 57:11.760
You must do good things for humans for three hundred years

57:11.760 --> 57:16.760
and then you can have an immortal soul and be with God.

57:46.760 --> 57:49.760
You must do good things for humans.

